b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.88759ed0-4ece-4dc7-b909-2c4b7815ea60.description=Waits for the job to reach a specific state. If no state is specified, then this will wait for the job to reach an end state. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - The id of the job. status - The status to wait for the job to reach. If none is specified this will wait until the job is no longer running. timeout - The maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the job. If not specified, 1 hour is used. frequency - The frequency, in milliseconds, with which the operation will check if the job has reached the specified state (or an end state). The default value is 5000 ms. Responses\: failure - Something went wrong. success - The operation completed successfully. b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.a79e03d6-0e52-4b0a-bb88-34c693eb2100.description=Counts from one number to another number. 
Inputs\:
count - number of loops to complete
reset - If true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.
failure - Something went wrong.
b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.a90f19ca-6a19-49e6-aa1a-3d3faa114c3f.description=Use an apx command to deactivate a server from the Server Automation server (SAS). Internally this flow will use ssh for the protocol and port 2222 for the connection. Inputs\: coreHost - SAS core hostname or IP address coreUsername - SAS username to access the coreHost corePassword - SAS user's password to access the coreHost serverName - name of the managed server to be deactivated Responses\: success - operation completed successfully failure - otherwise b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.c37f0290-627a-4cb8-bd0b-c6238ea669b3.description=Retrieves the server(s) ServerVO properties Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. agent - The agent name search string (can be a partial name and multiple return results can be returned; the matching type for this input can be selected by using the 'matching' flag). matching - A flag that indicates if the search performed using the agent name should be based on a partial or exact match. The default value for this input is 'Begins With'. serverID - The ID of the searched server. This input should be used for unique identification. If provided, then the 'agent' input is ignored. delimiter - The delimiter used to separate the result values. By default the values are comma delimited. Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. id - The unique ID of this object. createdBy - The name of the user who created this object. createdDate - The date that this object was created. dirtyAttributes - A ; delimited list of attributes that are dirty (Modified and not yet fully propagated). modifiedBy - The user who last modified this object. modifiedDate - The date that this object was last modified on. description - The description of this object. hostname - The DNS hostname of this object. model - The model of this object. osVersion - The version of the OS running on the object. primaryIP - The primary IP address of this object. serialNumber - This object's serial number. manufacturer - The manufacturer of this object. name - The name of this object version - The version of this object codeset - The Code set of this object. customerName - The name of the customer this object was created for. defaultGW - The default gateway used when accessing this object. discoveredDate - The date when this object was first discovered. facilityName - The name of the facility housing this object. locale - The locale this object is in. lockComment - The comment on this object's locked. NOTE\: object may not be locked. lockDate - The date this object was last locked. lockUser - The user who locked this object last. isLocked - A boolean value specifying whether or not this object is currently locked. loopbackIP - The loopback ip address used by this object. managementIP - The management ip address used by this object. mid - mid The server's management identifier. NetBIOSName - The full netBIOS (Windows networking) name for this object. lifecycle - The state in the Opsware lifecycle that this object is currently in. origin - The origin of the managed server. ASSIMILATED or PROVISIONED osFlavor - The flavor of the OS running on this object. For example\: Windows. osSPVersion - The service pack version of the OS running on the object. peerIP - The managed server's peer IP address. platformName - The name of the platform. previousSWRegDate -The last time the Opsware agent reported the installed software on the server. realmName - The name of the realm this object is in. stage - The stage of the managed server. state - The current state of the managed server\: OK, UNREACHABLE or MAINTENANCE use - The intended use of the managed server (i.e. its role in a deployment)\: DEVELOPMENT, STAGING, PRODUCTION or UNKNOWN. virtualizationType - The virtualization type. b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.c7ae4db7-4949-4322-b47b-f90c1fe8a14f.description=Sleeps for "X" seconds. 
Inputs\:
seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for "X" seconds.
failure - was unable to sleep for some reason
b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.d00183f5-0ab0-41a3-b78b-c91caf3ae63b.description=Starts deploying an agent on an unmanaged server. This operation is supported from SA version 10.1 (sas101). Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. serverIPAddress - The IP address of the server on which the agent will be installed. protocol - Set the protocol used to login to the server on which the agent will be installed. If set to 'Select automatically', the job will try every protocol possible and use the first which is available. Possible values are\: ssh, telnet, netbt, rlogin. protocolPort - Set the port for the protocol specified above. If not set, the default port for the protocol will be used. username - The username for the server on which the agent will be installed. password - The password for the server on which the agent will be installed. rootPassword - Specify in case authentication is done as a non-root user, to become root (UNIX only). Set the value 'sudo' if the user is in the sudoers group, otherwise set the root password. actionType - Select the action type\: 'check' for checking if prerequisite conditions are fulfilled, 'download' for checking if prerequisite conditions are fulfilled and staging(downloading) the Agent installer binary or 'install' for checking if the prerequisite conditions are fulfilled, staging(downloading) the Agent installer binary and running the Agent installer binary. Default is 'install'. targetOSClass - Set the target OS class for the server on which the agent will be installed. Valid values are\: Windows, UNIX. realmName - The name of the realm. If set, the gateway inputs will be ignored. realmID - The ID of the realm. If set, the 'realmName' and the gateway inputs will be ignored. gatewayName - The name of the gateway. If set, the 'gatewayAddressInfo' must be specified. gatewayID - The ID of the gateway. If set, the 'gatewayAddressInfo' must be specified and the 'gatewayName' will be ignored. gatewayAddressInfo - The IP addresses and proxy ports of the gateways, in the format \:, separated by 'separator'. The IP addresses can be either version 4 (e.g. 192.168.55.22\:100) or version 6, which must be enclosed in brackets (e.g. [ff\:\:]\:100). If set, the gateway name or ID must be specified. noStartAgent - Do not start agent after installation. Default value is false. ignorePrerequisiteCheckFailures - Specify whether the deployment process should ignore any prerequisites check failures and proceed with the Agent installation. Default value is false. setTime - Set system time from HP Server Automation core. Default value is false. installMSI - Install Windows installer (MSI) if required (Windows only). Default value is false. reboot - Reboot at completion of successful install if warranted (Windows only). Default value is false. installRPM - Install Red Hat Package Manager (RPM) if required (AIX/Solaris only). Default value is false. resetConf - Reset agent configuration file to default settings. Default value is false. noOpswareGateway - Indicate that no Opsware gateway is necessary. Default value is false. overwriteInstaller - Specify whether HP SA Agent installer binary should be overwritten in case already staged. Default value is false. logLevel - The log level. Log levels are\: error, trace, warning, info. Default value is error. forceFullHardwareRegistration - Force full hardware registration. Default value is false. forceSoftwareRegistration - Force software registration. Default value is false. noReachabilityCheck - Suppress agent reachability check. Default value is false. noAnonymousSSL - Disable anonymous SSL. Applies to dormant agent only. Default value is false. forceNewDevice - Force creation of new device record if conflict found. Default value is false. failOnHardwareRegistrationError - Fail if initial hardware registration fails (do not go dormant). Default value is false. doNotOpenWindowsFirewall - Set 'true' to not open Windows firewall for core-agent communications. Default value is false. remediateSoftwarePolicy - Perform a remediate of Software Policies after install. Default value is false. softwarePolicyID - The ID of the software policy to attach. fingerprint - Fingerprint of the peer's certificate. Default value is false. installerOptions - Set the command line arguments for the HP SA Agent installer. userTag - An user provided tag applicable to this job. timeout - The maximum time, in seconds, within which this method should complete and the operation should return. The job will fail with a timeout error if the Install HP SA Agent operation does not complete in the given number of seconds. The default value is 0 (no timeout). separator - The separator used for separating the inputs. The default value for the separator is a comma (,). notificationFailureOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job failed. notificationSuccessOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job succeeded. notificationCancelOwner - The email address of the owner of the job when the job was canceled. notificationFailureRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job failed. notificationSuccessRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job succeeded. notificationCancelRecipients - The email addresses to notify when the job was canceled. scheduleDateYear - The year to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule. scheduleDateMonth - The month to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 1 and 12. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule. scheduleDateDayOfMonth - The day to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 1 and 31. This input must be provided for setting a job schedule. scheduleDateHour - The hour to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 23. If not set, if will have the default value 0. scheduleDateMinute - The minute to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 59. If not set, if will have the default value 0. scheduleDateSecond - The second to be used for setting the date when the job is scheduled to start. It should have the value between 0 and 59. If not set, if will have the default value 0. scheduleDateTimezone - The time zone used to express the job schedule date. If not set, it will have the default value GMT. Outputs\: jobId - The ID of the job created for installing a HP SA Agent on a server. Responses\: success - The operation has completed successfully. failure - The operation has failed. b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.description=server.os\: Windows or UNIX b1fc52da-9756-44fc-9a4c-544ba28b2eba.e7455ba2-56dc-4c3e-a26a-aef17786fda9.description=Retrieves the server(s) ServerVO properties Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with.
